{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-projects-page-js","path":"/projects/raspberry-pi-screenly/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I was asked to install the first digital marketing screen at the Fitzwilliam Museum with 2 days notice, just before the\nreopening of gallery 3 (this went alongside all the work we were putting in on <a href=\"/content/projects/beyond-the-label\">enhanced labels</a>).</p>\n<p>We purchased an <a href=\"https://www.iiyama-monitors.co.uk\">Iiyama touch screen</a> (not using that bit yet), and connected a <a href=\"https://www.raspberrypi.com/products/raspberry-pi-4-model-b/\">Raspberry Pi 4</a> that I donated to the Museum and <a href=\"https://www.screenly.io/ose/\">Screenly's Open Source Edition</a>.\nThe purpose of the screen wasn't fully defined at the point of installation, but the marketing team wanted to\ndisplay a video loop of the Museum's exhibitions and events.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 2000px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 89.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/4be29/install.webp 500w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/03f31/install.webp 1000w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/b1218/install.webp 2000w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/27bed/install.webp 3000w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/5312e/install.webp 3288w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/d1f95/install.jpg 500w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/dbdff/install.jpg 1000w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/109c0/install.jpg 2000w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/9a593/install.jpg 3000w,\n/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/e037f/install.jpg 3288w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/656b945ed9c70da30415ee2563b5602f/109c0/install.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Installing the screen\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Installing the screen</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The solution for this project cost £845 - the screen was about £800, Pi about £40 and fixtures about £5.\nSet up for the screen took a couple of hours due to the trickiness of getting the machine to <a href=\"https://www.instructables.com/Access-Eduroam-on-a-Raspberry-Pi-in-Cambridge/\">connect to Eduroam</a> within\nthe museum's estate (at the point of install, the museum network had not been upgraded) and getting it to stay connected to the Wi-Fi.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/db98d4aac8cedf00b29583fbf8aad670/4be29/screenlySetUp.webp 500w,\n/static/db98d4aac8cedf00b29583fbf8aad670/03f31/screenlySetUp.webp 1000w,\n/static/db98d4aac8cedf00b29583fbf8aad670/9579c/screenlySetUp.webp 1500w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/db98d4aac8cedf00b29583fbf8aad670/d1f95/screenlySetUp.jpg 500w,\n/static/db98d4aac8cedf00b29583fbf8aad670/dbdff/screenlySetUp.jpg 1000w,\n/static/db98d4aac8cedf00b29583fbf8aad670/9d81f/screenlySetUp.jpg 1500w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/db98d4aac8cedf00b29583fbf8aad670/9d81f/screenlySetUp.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Setting up Screenly on my macbook\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Setting up Screenly on my macbook</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 81.8%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/4be29/pi.webp 500w,\n/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/03f31/pi.webp 1000w,\n/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/9579c/pi.webp 1500w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/d1f95/pi.jpg 500w,\n/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/dbdff/pi.jpg 1000w,\n/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/9d81f/pi.jpg 1500w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/9d81f/pi.jpg\"\n            alt=\"The Raspberry Pi connected\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The Raspberry Pi connected</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Images and video are rotated 90 degrees to the right to fit the screen which has been installed in portrait mode\n(this had a better effect on the device than rotating the screen software side.) Content is rotated every 30 seconds and listed to\nchange and expire based on the date and time.</p>\n<p>The device is scheduled to turn off automatically at the end of the day, but I've noticed that the Front of House staff tend to turn it off manually at the socket at the end of opening hours.</p>\n<h2>Where can I find this screen?</h2>\n<p>The screen is located in the Museum's main entrance, and has been fitted to the stud wall with a bracket and then an old\npicture frame was used to hide the bezels of the screen and to hold the Raspberry Pi in place. The sockets were luckily in place for\nthe security team to easily install the screen and not create new work for the maintenance crew.</p>\n<h2>An example of content displayed</h2>\n<div class=\"ratio-16x9 ratio\">\n<video controls>\n  <source src=\"/video/welcomescreen.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">\n</video> \n</div>","id":"929a8f76-83fb-50da-af23-a02b709f9e04","timeToRead":1,"wordCount":{"words":343},"frontmatter":{"date":"October 04, 2019","section":"projects","title":"Raspberry Pi x Screenly","description":"A Raspberry Pi based digital signage solution","role":null,"featuredImg":{"id":"12d0db75-ba83-5553-8d1b-94415dfb517a","absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/museologi.st/museologi.st/content/images/2019/screenly.jpg","publicURL":"/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/screenly.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/04add/screenly.jpg","srcSet":"/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/e07d1/screenly.jpg 150w,\n/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/05177/screenly.jpg 300w,\n/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/04add/screenly.jpg 600w","sizes":"(min-width: 600px) 600px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/628fd/screenly.webp 150w,\n/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/8aaca/screenly.webp 300w,\n/static/7fd6716d1f144a9b244e5f44a2447ae4/ec39e/screenly.webp 600w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 600px) 600px, 100vw"}]},"width":600,"height":600}}},"featuredImgAlt":null,"partners":null,"collaborators":null,"institution":"The Fitzwilliam Museum","publications":null,"geo_lat":null,"geo_lon":null,"news":null,"background":{"id":"8befe977-ea1b-546c-b1d9-4e4b39e753ad","absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/museologi.st/museologi.st/content/images/2019/10/pi.jpg","publicURL":"/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/pi.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/8551d/pi.jpg","srcSet":"/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/487e9/pi.jpg 300w,\n/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/1d415/pi.jpg 600w,\n/static/7c10de1abb14ae2a3c8d4b8e0cd111fe/8551d/pi.jpg 1200w","sizes":"(min-width